                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280529-259-off1422 t18280529-259-victim1397"></join>
                     </persName>
                  , from his person
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>WILLIAM TAYLOR. On Thursday last, about one o'clock in the day, I was near <placeName id="t18280529-259-crimeloc1424">Holborn-hill</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18280529-259-crimeloc1424" type="placeName" value="Holborn-hill"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18280529-259-crimeloc1424" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280529-259-off1422 t18280529-259-crimeloc1424"></join>; I felt some one pulling at my pocket - I turned round, but did not observe anybody: a little boy told me that the prisoner had taken my handkerchief; he was then playing on the pavement with money; I challenged him with it - he denied it, and said if I would let go of his collar he would walk with me; I let him go; he ran from me - a gentleman stopped him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280529-259-person1398">
                  JAMES 
                  HARVEY DAVIES
               <interp inst="t18280529-259-person1398" type="surname" value="HARVEY DAVIES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280529-259-person1398" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280529-259-person1398" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I saw the prisoner take the handkerchief, and give it to another boy, who ran down Field-lane with it - it was a yellow handkerchief, and I think had some white spots on it; I do not think there was any red or blue in it - I did not tell Mr. Taylor sooner, because I thought they would beat me.</p>
               <p>WILLIAM TAYLOR. My handkerchief was yellow, with white birds' eyes on it; I have not seen it since; this little boy seemed very much frightened.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280529-259-person1399">
                  JOHN 
                  LAWS
               <interp inst="t18280529-259-person1399" type="surname" value="LAWS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280529-259-person1399" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280529-259-person1399" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a patrol. The prisoner was delivered to me.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I had been out of work, and was<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182805290109"></xptr>going to Drury-lane to get some bottles; this gentleman said I had his handkerchief - I said I had not, and this boy said I took it.</p>
               <p>
